Here is a simple Java-based To-Do List mobile application using Android Studio:

1. Project Setup
Open Android Studio and create a new project.

Select "Empty Activity" and name your project (e.g., ToDoListApp).

Set the language to Java.

2. Layout Files
activity_main.xml
This file defines the main layout with a ListView to display tasks and a FloatingActionButton to add new tasks.Build and run the app on an emulator or physical device.
3. MainActivity.java
This file manages the app's functionality
Use the floating action button to add tasks, which will appear in the ListView.

This app provides basic functionality for creating and displaying tasks. You can enhance it further by adding features like task deletion or persistence using SQLite or SharedPreferences.
